children.subject: Yes! Agreed, super helpful.
<md>Thank you for making these master posts. It helps to keep the discussion organized and in one place.</md>
I didn't see the option for Data 8 on the department application either.
Not all course applications are available yet. This post and the department website will be updated as more applications become available.
<md>Poet, add yourself to the Data 001 Piazza. The first pinned post is the application for all Tutor/uGSI apps for Fall 2021: https://piazza.com/class/j7s01y165odq5?cid=3667</md>
Yeah refer to Data 001 for apps regarding most of the data science classes
Is the Data 8 ugsi/tutor application available yet?

<md>for 61a, you should fill out the departmental application -- there usually isn't a supplemental application except for summer hiring. i might be wrong, but i think 61b sends their supplemental application out after the departmental deadline.</md>
Will cs 61a or cs 61b be hiring for Fall 2021?

All courses are supposed to have hiring done by June 1. For 61c specifically, we will not be doing our hiring until the end of May because we will not start interviewing candidates until after finals in order to not add to student stress. I'm not sure about other courses
I know it's going to vary by course, but what's usually the rough hiring timeline for Fall? Do they generally aim to hire all Fall TAs by end of Spring semester?
Is the CS 10 application supposed to be closed? It says it's no longer accepting responses.
Last semester, they emailed it to people who applied using the department ASE app. Afaik, there wasn't a piazza post about it.
When is the CS70 supplemental application coming?
We are currently planning on having AIs in the labs, but it's possible that will change (i.e. no guarantees at this point).
Will there be announcements for AI applications?
Will 61a hire AI for fall?
Yep they are the same thing! uGSI just refers to a GSI/TA that's an undergraduate student.
uGSI = TA? Or are they different positions?
Any updates on when 61B will release its supplemental?

Yeah, we're accepting applications through the department form (we don't have a supplemental form for now). Fair warning though, we have a lot of PhD students in the fall who have hiring priority, so we may not have a lot of space to hire new undergrads.
Is 161 hiring for the fall?
I believe they sent out supplemental applications a while back directly to those who filled out the ASE form (and those were due a while back).
is 188 hiring for the fall?

yup this was posted on the cs70 piazza:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd0Cw4lO51h1ls1uS3u7lTFZU5QWcwVjSmoSvtZ1PnY0bmBlA/viewform
Yup we just released it, and I've updated this post accordingly.
Has the CS 70 reader supplemental application come out yet?
It seems that the cs10 form is closed.
I received an email today if you are referring to the summer session.
Fall AI hiring will be done much later, probably a couple weeks before the start of the semester
<md>Any updates on 61B AI Applications?</md>
from what I know, requests have been made, offer letters should be coming soon
Any update regarding 61A new uGSI hiring?
yes
In general, will readers for summer 2021 and fall 2021 be paid?
I received a TA offer from an upper div already
+1 but an informal offer, I believe formal offers are still waiting to be sent out
^woops same, it was an informal offer from the class email, no official offer letter yet
Is there an estimate when offers will come out?
Is it too late if I apply right now for 70? I didn't realize applications had come so early.
I was originally only considering to reader/tutor for the fall semester, but I decided to include uGSI roles as well. Is it too late for courses like 61A, 61B, and 70?
It depends on the class - ask the head TA or instructor for your class. Returning TAs are usually pretty common in the department though.
How does it work for returning TAs from summer positions?

We have communicated to the department our requests for TAs, and hope that offers will come soon from the department. We have not yet requested any offers to be sent to tutors, we will do so after the TAs are confirmed.
So, 61A doesn't have supplemental form/interview same as before?
never did, except for summer
Updates on the CS61A staff?
Are 61B AI offers still rolling out or does no email mean rejection?
Your application was still considered. As of this week we have finalized the vast majority of positions.
I submitted the 70 supplemental app past the deadline a little. Does that kill my chances of getting a position. Also, when can we expect to get acceptances/rejections?
We are still waiting for the department to send out offers
Just heard that some friends got their official 61C TA offers
Please note that not all offers have gone out yet. We can post a comment here once all offers have gone out.
Have all fall 61C offers gone out? When's the latest we can expect to hear back?
Have there been updates for Fall 61C course staff?
TAs have been notified
what's the timelines in case we haven't received an offer yet?
I just got my 61A TA offer yesterday, so it seems some offers are still being sent out.
Any update for CS61A Course Staff?
I got an unofficial offer for another upper div and haven't received an official offer yet, maybe upper divs are later
I received an offer for an upper div course yesterday
170 TA offers have been sent out
Any update on 170/189?

For this semester it is not allowed due to a new policy. You can be an ASE for at most one class. ASE includes being a TA.

However idk if that's enough to say why you didn't receive any other offers unless you were expecting more (i.e. u had more unofficial ones)
I only received that one unofficial offer, so I don't know whether the other classes I applied to are aware of that unofficial offer thus declined my application.

I received an email from the department informing me that I had received multiple offers from different classes. They said that since I was only allowed to teach for 1 class (I could accept only one appointment), I would have to let them know which class I wanted to teach for. 

the department has said that classes are not supposed to send unofficial offers; if a class has sent you one, this does not affect the departments process so I would assume you would still be contacted if you received another offer.
does anyone know where the new policy about being an ASE for one class is listed?
+1 @scale 4, where is this information?
To me it was on the offer email I received from the department.
Are multiple uGSI offers allowed? I received and accepted an unofficial uGSI offer several weeks ago and didn't receive any more offers afterwards, is that due to my acceptation of the other offer?

i believe 16a has finished hiring and has notified everyone (they have not sent out rejections yet though so they probably are using those who have been ghosted as a waitlist of sorts when people renege — which is a bigger concern this semester due to the only 1 ase limit rule),

16b has decided but has not notified people but has submitted them to the dept afaik

I just sent out all of the reader and tutor position offers that I had been given for 16A and 16B by course staff over the last couple of days. Reader and tutor hires for various courses are happening now but have not all happened since they are being handled by different staff with different courseloads, and it also depends on the information we have from course staff.
Any update on 16A/B for tutor and reader positions?
We have sent the majority of the offers for TAs and have not sent any offers for tutors yet. We have no readers for 61A.
Whom can we contact to get more information about CS61A course staff and the waitlist for tutors/readers?
Any updates on 61b course staff?
No 61A tutor offers have been sent yet. Probably not for at least another week.
Have 61A and 61B tutor offers been sent out yet?
Have 162 reader offers been sent?
Have 170 reader offers been sent?
61a tutor offers are rolling out -- we have some remaining to send, but a good chunk have been sent
Are we notified if we don't receive a tutor offer?
Any update as to when the remaining will be sent? Wondering whether to accept a different job or wait until I hear about 61a tutor
Have 61A tutor offers been sent out?
Is the 61C AI form date "apply by July 1st" correct? Are they still accepting applications? Also, are 61C labs planned to be in person?
Will there be a similar post like this for Spring 2021?

The ASE application will remain open into the Fall semester. We encourage students to apply as soon as possible since faculty and staff will begin reviewing applications after the 5/2 deadline. Any remaining applications will be evaluated on a rolling basis.

This post will be updated as more applications become available.
